## ?? Best Practices

? **DO:**
- Run multiple times and average results
- Compare same algorithm in both modes
- Use slow mode for teaching (visual clarity)
- Use fast mode for benchmarking (baseline)
- Copy and save important metrics

? **DON'T:**
- Rely on single run (system variance)
- Run during heavy CPU load (skewed results)
- Close metrics label during analysis
- Clear metrics without saving
- Run slow mode for extended periods (very slow)

